divs: Sighting Detailswe where coming into the dock area from fishing, it had just got dark. I was watching a satellite glide across the night sky when i noticed a bright, star like object floating across the sky. It wasn't flashing, it was solid white. then another one followed behind it. you could tell that they where pretty high, but still the brightest thing in the sky by far. We watched them for 4 or 5 minuets, we where all so mesmerized by it, we hit a group of small rocks, sticking out of the water. then, one by one, they faded away.
